calcuale diamiter

basal_area <- total_plots %>%
  gather("d_10", "diamiter", starts_with ("d_"))%>%
  mutate(basal_area = (diamiter*0.5)^2*3.14159265359)%>%
  arrange(tree)%>%
  filter(!is.na(diamiter))
 
  

#combind basal area for multi stemmed trees 
 ind_biomass <- basal_area%>%
  group_by(tree, height, landform, plots, rainfall, subplot, sub_plot_area, subplot_density, plot_density)%>%
  summarise(basal_area = sum(basal_area),.groups = "drop")%>%
  mutate(
     #back tranform total_basal_area to diamiter 
    diamiter =  case_when(rainfall == "low" ~ (sqrt(basal_area/3.14159265359))*2,
                          rainfall == "moderate" ~ (sqrt(basal_area/3.14159265359))*2,
    # transform to do DBH for high rainfall sites -> equation adapted from Fensham et al 2012 "Potential aboveground biomass in drought-prone forest used for rangeland pastoralism" pg 4 dbh = d30/1.2125 
                          rainfall == "high" ~ ((sqrt(basal_area/3.14159265359))*2)/1.2125),
    
    # Equations taken from -> Paul et al, "testing the generality of above ground ind_biomass allometry across plant funcitoal types at the continent scale" -> Fmulti "ln(AGB) = 2.474ln(D10)-2.757" used for lower rainfall sites (page 9)
    # second equation taken paul and roxburgh 2013 "Development and testing of allometric equation for estimating above-ground biomass of mixed-species environmental plantings" (see table 4 acacia tree)
    logAGB = case_when(rainfall == 'low' ~ 2.474*log(diamiter)-2.757,
                      rainfall == 'moderate' ~ 2.474*log(diamiter)-2.757,
                      rainfall == 'high' ~ 2.19*log(diamiter)-1.59),
    # correctional factors taken form relevant equations in respective papers. CF for high rainfall taken form average of Acacia trees paul and roxburgh 2013.
    AGB = case_when( rainfall == 'low' ~ exp(logAGB)*1.0787,
                     rainfall == 'moderate' ~ exp(logAGB)*1.0787,
                     rainfall == 'high' ~ exp(logAGB)*1.02))

 
#plot level biomass
plot_biomass <- ind_biomass%>%
  aggregate(AGB ~ subplot + landform + sub_plot_area + plots + rainfall + subplot_density + plot_density, sum)%>%
  mutate(
    biomass.m2 = AGB/sub_plot_area,
    logbiomass.m2 = log(biomass.m2),
    log.sub.dens = log(subplot_density))
ind_biomass%>%
  mutate(basal_area = as.numeric(basal_area))

#lme4

f.ind_biomass <- filter(ind_biomass, diamiter > 1.0)
fit <- lmer(logAGB ~ landform + rainfall + (1|plots), data = f.ind_biomass, REML = T)

qqnorm(residuals(fit), pch = 1, frame = FALSE)
qqline(residuals(fit), col = "steelblue", lwd = 2)

scatter.smooth(residuals(fit) ~ fitted(fit))

fit <- lmer(logAGB ~ landform + rainfall + (1|plots), data = ind_biomass, REML = F)
fit_null <- lmer(logAGB ~ landform + (1|plots), data = ind_biomass)

anova(fit_null,fit,test = "LRT")
## refitting model(s) with ML (instead of REML)
